50// The key in a script cache is a WeakFixedArray containing a weak pointer to
51// the Script. The corresponding value can be either the root SharedFunctionInfo
52// or undefined. The purpose of storing the root SharedFunctionInfo as the value
53// is to keep it alive, not to save a lookup on the Script. A newly added entry
54// always contains the root SharedFunctionInfo. After the root
55// SharedFunctionInfo has aged sufficiently, it is replaced with undefined. In
56// this way, all strong references to large objects are dropped, but there is
57// still a way to get the Script if it happens to still be alive.
58class ScriptCacheKey : public HashTableKey {
59 public:
60 enum Index {
61 kHash,
62 kWeakScript,
63 kEnd,
64 };
65
66 ScriptCacheKey(Handle<String> source, const ScriptDetails* script_details,
67 Isolate* isolate);
68 ScriptCacheKey(Handle<String> source, MaybeHandle<Object> name,
69 int line_offset, int column_offset,
70 v8::ScriptOriginOptions origin_options,
71 MaybeHandle<Object> host_defined_options,
72 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> maybe_wrapped_arguments,
73 Isolate* isolate);
74
75 bool IsMatch(Tagged<Object> other) override;
76 bool MatchesScript(Tagged<Script> script);
77
78 Handle<Object> AsHandle(Isolate* isolate, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared);
79
80 static base::Optional<Tagged<String>> SourceFromObject(Tagged<Object> obj) {
81 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
82 DCHECK(IsWeakFixedArray(obj));
83 Tagged<WeakFixedArray> array = WeakFixedArray::cast(obj);
84 DCHECK_EQ(array->length(), kEnd);
85
86 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_script = array->get(kWeakScript);
87 if (Tagged<HeapObject> script; maybe_script.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&script)) {
88 Tagged<PrimitiveHeapObject> source_or_undefined =
89 Script::cast(script)->source();
90 // Scripts stored in the script cache should always have a source string.
91 return String::cast(source_or_undefined);
92 }
93
94 DCHECK(maybe_script.IsCleared());
95 return {};
96 }
97
98 private:
99 Handle<String> source_;
100 MaybeHandle<Object> name_;
101 int line_offset_;
102 int column_offset_;
103 v8::ScriptOriginOptions origin_options_;
104 MaybeHandle<Object> host_defined_options_;
105 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> wrapped_arguments_;
106 Isolate* isolate_;
107};

112}

114uint32_t CompilationCacheShape::EvalHash(Tagged<String> source,
115 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
116 LanguageMode language_mode,
117 int position) {
118 uint32_t hash = source->EnsureHash();
119 if (shared->HasSourceCode()) {
120 // Instead of using the SharedFunctionInfo pointer in the hash
121 // code computation, we use a combination of the hash of the
122 // script source code and the start position of the calling scope.
123 // We do this to ensure that the cache entries can survive garbage
124 // collection.
125 Tagged<Script> script(Script::cast(shared->script()));
126 hash ^= String::cast(script->source())->EnsureHash();
127 }
128 static_assert(LanguageModeSize == 2);
129 if (is_strict(language_mode)) hash ^= 0x8000;
130 hash += position;
131 return hash;
132}
133
134uint32_t CompilationCacheShape::HashForObject(ReadOnlyRoots roots,
135 Tagged<Object> object) {
136 // Eval: The key field contains the hash as a Number.
137 if (IsNumber(object)) return static_cast<uint32_t>(Object::Number(object));
138
139 // Code: The key field contains the SFI key.
140 if (IsSharedFunctionInfo(object)) {
141 return SharedFunctionInfo::cast(object)->Hash();
142 }
143
144 // Script.
145 if (IsWeakFixedArray(object)) {
146 return static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::ToInt(
147 WeakFixedArray::cast(object)->get(ScriptCacheKey::kHash).ToSmi()));
148 }
149
150 // Eval: See EvalCacheKey::ToHandle for the encoding.
151 Tagged<FixedArray> val = FixedArray::cast(object);
152 if (val->map() == roots.fixed_cow_array_map()) {
153 DCHECK_EQ(4, val->length());
154 Tagged<String> source = String::cast(val->get(1));
155 int language_unchecked = Smi::ToInt(val->get(2));
156 DCHECK(is_valid_language_mode(language_unchecked));
157 LanguageMode language_mode = static_cast<LanguageMode>(language_unchecked);
158 int position = Smi::ToInt(val->get(3));
159 Tagged<Object> shared = val->get(0);
160 return EvalHash(source, SharedFunctionInfo::cast(shared), language_mode,
161 position);
162 }
163
164 // RegExp: The key field (and the value field) contains the
165 // JSRegExp::data fixed array.
166 DCHECK_GE(val->length(), JSRegExp::kMinDataArrayLength);
167 return RegExpHash(String::cast(val->get(JSRegExp::kSourceIndex)),
168 Smi::cast(val->get(JSRegExp::kFlagsIndex)));
169}
